rComments: This class was a "special topic" and Shamanism was definitely something he would teach about (had a section of this during his ANT318 field school). No textbook (instead there are articles that he provides links to) so it is mandatory to attend class. He is overall a fair marker (only an essay)and good prof.
Field school was awesome! Funny and very interested in what he does. However he is disorganized  and sounds like a hippie. Would take other classes of his!
Really fun class! I would do the field school again if I could. He was a little disorganized, but considering it was his first year teaching this, very well done.  He is very approachable & helpful.
Great, would take the course again.
